message.content:
A Calidris minutilla is a small shorebird commonly known as the Least Sandpiper.
It has a brownish or grayish upper body, and a white underbelly.
Its bill is relatively short and thin.
The Calidris minutilla has black legs and small, dark eyes.
It measures around 13 to 15.5 centimeters in length and weighs about 20 grams.
This species can be found in wetlands, marshes, and mud flats throughout North America and parts of South America.
They feed mainly on small invertebrates, such as insects and crustaceans.
